node.text: Affirmation of the Day: I won't stop going, even if I'm the only one who believes in my dreams. In my moments of feeling lack and doubt, I will change the story I tell myself. I know my mind is full of brilliant ideas that have the power to benefit myself and others. Every challenge, every loss, and every success is a learning lesson that brings me closer to my goals. I got this. 🧡 Which reminders are resonating with you today?

node.text: Affirmation of the Day: I am not in control of others, how they think, how they feel, what they do - and that is okay. I release the need to be. I am, however, in control of my life, my proximity to what doesn’t align with my values, and my perspective. It’s good to feel good. I am worthy. I am on my way. 🧡

node.text:
After qualifying in the olympic trials last month as one of the fastest women in the world, Sha'Carri Richardson was suspended from competing for testing positive for THC. She admitted to using marijuana, which is legal/decriminalized in several states across the country, to cope with her mother's death just days before. Sha'Carri will be cleared in time to potentially run for the US team's 4x100 relay after her suspension, but her qualifying time for the 100-meter race was invalidated.
caption/first slide: @katieisdoodling
